name: io.bytes.per.checksum
description:
The number of bytes per checksum.  Must not be larger than
  io.file.buffer.size.

name: mapreduce.job.end-notification.retry.attempts
description:
The number of times the submitter of the job wants to retry job
    end notification if it fails. This is capped by
    mapreduce.job.end-notification.max.attempts

name: dfs.datanode.du.reserved.pct
description:
Reserved space in percentage. Read dfs.datanode.du.reserved.calculator to see
    when this takes effect. The actual number of bytes reserved will be calculated by using the
    total capacity of the data directory in question. Specific storage type based reservation
    is also supported. The property can be followed with corresponding storage types
    ([ssd]/[disk]/[archive]/[ram_disk]) for cluster with heterogeneous storage.
    For example, reserved percentage space for RAM_DISK storage can be configured using property
    'dfs.datanode.du.reserved.pct.ram_disk'. If specific storage type reservation is not configured
    then dfs.datanode.du.reserved.pct will be used.

name: dfs.datanode.min.outlier.detection.disks
description: Minimum number of disks to run outlier detection.

name: yarn.app.mapreduce.client.max-retries
description:
The number of client retries to the RM/HS before
    throwing exception. This is a layer above the ipc.

name: dfs.storage.policy.satisfier.retry.max.attempts
description:
Max retry to satisfy the block storage policy. After this retry block will be removed
    from the movement needed queue.

name: ha.health-monitor.connect-retry-interval.ms
description: How often to retry connecting to the service.

name: dfs.client.socketcache.capacity
description:
Socket cache capacity (in entries) for short-circuit reads.
    If this value is set to 0, the client socket cache is disabled.

name: mapreduce.job.encrypted-intermediate-data-key-size-bits
description: Mapreduce encrypt data key size default is 128
